This app is an attempt to make a controller through the Android interface Linked to the system inputs , via a python backend server
i made this app just to play Hollow Knight cause my keyboard would die if i played the game on it.

This app has a logic based on webport , https signals and pyautogui input -- > output conversion , the backend server logic was 
developed using python ( cause i love that language ) , and the external GUI and interface was developed using flask and Dart(Java)
because they were more reliable for my purpose than react or any web based app cause , an android app enable much more controls 
than a web port.

This was a project done entirely out of passion and the drive to play hollow knight therefore it is not perfect rn, i plan to 
add a few more buttons on the gamepad version but other than that the game is playable , and this was also an attempt to prove 
my proffessor wrong so i guess a win win.

This is also my Second Time Uploading on to Git Hub, i have made apps prior to this but they were of miniscule importance and 
moreover i was also not informed about git hub. Currently this is my first personal project on the app so treat this as a beginners 
